notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger; alternative title from caption title (f. 2v).
Blue paper pasted to the last page is written from Mirzā Muḥammad Khān ʻĪsā Khān from the madrasah Dār al-Shafā to Karbālāʼī Muḥammad Haydar.

Customs stamp dated 1312; numerous owner's stamps and notes (first flyleaf recto at front of book and f. 2v). Owner's note dated 1226 A.H. with the name Mullā ʻIsá walad Karbālāʼī Muḥammad Ḥaydar? (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: One volume, incomplete, of a Qurʼān exegesis in Persian; last legible verse is 115 of al-Māʼidah with the commentary partially pasted over.

msItem.title: Jalāʼ al-adhhān wa-jalāʼ al-aḥzān fī tafsīr al-Qurʼān.
]جلاء الاذهان وجلاء الاحزان فى تفسير القرآن[

respStmt.persName: ʻĪsá walad Karbālāʼī Muḥammad Ḥaydar, active 1811

msItem.title: [Jalāʼ al-az̲hān wa-jalāʼ al-aḥzān fī tafsīr al-Qurʼān].

supportDesc.extent: 204 unfoliated leaves : 300 x 185 (215 x 130) mm, bound to 300 x 185 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 29 lines per pages except the first two pages (24 and 20 lines per page).

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written chiefly in nastaʻlīq with Arabic in naskh with vocalization.

decoDesc.decoNote: Rubrications, including some Arabic, in red; overlines in red.

binding.p: Black leather over pasteboard with blind-stamped central mandorla and two pendants on the vertical axis, two paper onlays remain on the back cover; blind tooled radiant lines and border; pastedowns covered in pen tests, notes and stamps.

origin.p: Item is undated; perhaps copied in the 16th or 17th century.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by ʻIsá walad Karbālāʼī Muḥammad Ḥaydar (f. 1r).
Formerly owned by David Eugene Smith (note in pencil f. 1v).
